setOft.t.sol
├── when caller does not have the relevant role
│  └── it should revert with AccessManagedUnauthorized
└── when caller has the relevant role
   ├── when the provided oft address is equal to zero
   │  └── it should revert with ZeroTokenAddress
   └── when the provided oft address is not equal to zero
      ├── it should register the provided oft address for its corresponding token
      ├── it should overwrite any previously registered oft for the provided OFT's associated token
      └── it should emit a OftRegistered event
